The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, July 14: Foreign exchange reserves increased by $1.34 billion for the week ended July 6 to $214.83 billion against $213.48 billion in the previous week. Foreign currency assets increased by $1.47 billion to $207.58 billion during the week ended June 29. FCAs in dollars include the effect of revaluation of non-US currencies such as euro, sterling and yen held in reserves.Gold reserves, however, were down by $124 million to $6.78 billion for the week ended July 6. Special drawing rights remained static at $1 million. 

 Mumbai, July 14: The RBI has directed all commercial banks to reduce interest rates on export finance by two percentage points following the governments decision to grant subsidy to exporters hit hard by the rise in the rupee value.




